-System hardening (windows, linux, iOS, Android, etc.) -> updates, user credential (username, passwords), limit network access, anti-malware, anti-virus, encryption.
-Endpoint detection and response (EDR): its a tool that monitor and respond to threats on endpoints (laptops, desktops, servers, etc.) It responds by isolating affected endpoints, removing malicious files or 
rolling back changes made by malware.
-Host-based firewall
-Open ports and services: have those limited as what is necessary. We can use nmap to scan which ports are open
-Change the default passwords
-Remove unnecessary software
